. I'm not sure that you really can. The `martini.Params` service only makes sense in the context of a _matched route_, which is what determines the parameter names and values. But middleware doesn't really have any concept of which route is matched.

Instead, you can achieve something similar by just adding handlers to your routes. Here's a full example:

``` go
package main

import (
    "fmt"

    "github.com/go-martini/martini"
)

func middleware(c martini.Context, params martini.Params) {
    fmt.Println("Middleware")
}

func main() {
    m := martini.Classic()
    m.Get("/", middleware, func() string {
        return "Hello, world!"
    })
    m.Run()
}
```
