. I think thing here is to realize that the keys of `martini.Params` are taken straight from the named capture groups of the regex. As @mvader pointed out, the full regex ends up looking something like `(?P<id>[^/#?]+)([0-9]+)`. That is, `:name` is syntactic sugar for "bind a single piece of a URL to the name `name`."

So to get the behavior you want, just introduce the named capture directly. Here's a full working example:

``` go
package main

import (
    "fmt"
    "log"

    "github.com/go-martini/martini"
)

func main() {
    m := martini.Classic()
    m.Get("/test/(?P<id>[0-9]+)", func(p martini.Params) string {
        return fmt.Sprintf("ID %s", p["id"])
    })
    m.Run()
}
```
